<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="118" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,258,931]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,258,283]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Thorax entirely black. Abdomen including terminalia black. Male tergite 
<number box="[1127,1141,259,283]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="8.0">8</number>
short, with shallow sinus anteriorly. Posterior cercus curved inward. Female: fore coxa black, remaining yellow; female and some males with hind femur black and yellow banded. 
<collectingCountry box="[632,688,330,355]" name="India" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia without pinnate setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="119" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,258,931]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,366,391]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Description</emphasis>
. 
<typeStatus box="[357,461,366,391]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Holotype</typeStatus>
male. Body length 2.3 mm; wing length 2.3 mm. Width of frons approximately subequal to anterior ocellus width. Antenna velvety black. Palpus brown. Thorax shiny black. Thoracic setae: 
<number box="[1394,1436,403,427]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
dorsocentrals, 
<number box="[315,357,439,463]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
antepronotals, 
<number box="[532,574,439,463]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
proepisternals, 
<number box="[754,796,439,463]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
pairs of scutellars. Legs shiny yellow with apex of hind femur, almost entire hind tibia and all tarsomeres 
<number box="[709,750,474,499]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
black. 
<collectingCountry box="[832,888,474,499]" name="India" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Hind</collectingCountry>
femur with 
<number box="[1026,1040,475,499]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="1.0">1</number>
anteroventral seta slightly stronger at distal third. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[413,501,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 54 – 63" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1580,1603]" captionTargetBox="[161,1436,193,1544]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[161,1446,193,1545]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54 – 63. Wings. 54, Macrostomus acreanus sp. nov. paratype ♂; 55, M. acreanus sp. nov. paratype ♀; 56, M. albicaudatus sp. nov. paratype ♂; 57, M. albicaudatus sp. nov. paratype ♀; 58, M. amazonensis sp. nov. paratype ♂; 59, M. amazonensis sp. nov. paratype ♀; 60, M. paraiba sp. nov. paratype ♂; 61, M. paraiba sp. nov. paratype ♀; 62, M. xavieri sp. nov. paratype ♂; 63, M. xavieri sp. nov. paratype ♀." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237986/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
Fig. 
<number box="[471,501,510,535]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="62.0">62</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<typeStatus box="[519,621,511,535]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">paratype</typeStatus>
). Halter dark brown, partially white at knob. Abdomen shiny black. Terminalia with tergite 
<number box="[420,434,547,571]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[452,535,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURES 45 – 53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1842,1865]" captionTargetBox="[191,1395,983,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,983,1820]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 45 – 53. Macrostomus xavieri, sp. nov. 45 – 49, paratype ♂. 45, tergite 8, dorsal view, right setae omitted; 46, epandrium detached, lateral view (gray colored); 47, hypandrium and cerci (cerci gray colored, tergite 8 setae omitted), lateral view; 48, ventral projection of cerci with developed expansion, anterodorsal view; 49, cercal bridge connecting anterior cerci, anterodorsal view, setae omitted; 50 – 53, paratype ♀. 50, tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view, setae omitted; 51, tergite 8, dorsal view; 52, sternite 8, ventral view; 53, genital fork, ventral view. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus: BS, baciliform sclerite; VPC, ventral projection of cercus. Scales: 45 – 49, 50 – 52 = 0.2 mm; 53 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237985/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
Fig. 
<number box="[506,535,546,571]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="45.0">45</number>
</figureCitation>
) short, without sinus posteriorly and with shallow sinus anteriorly. Epandrium (
<figureCitation box="[159,240,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 45 – 53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1842,1865]" captionTargetBox="[191,1395,983,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,983,1820]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 45 – 53. Macrostomus xavieri, sp. nov. 45 – 49, paratype ♂. 45, tergite 8, dorsal view, right setae omitted; 46, epandrium detached, lateral view (gray colored); 47, hypandrium and cerci (cerci gray colored, tergite 8 setae omitted), lateral view; 48, ventral projection of cerci with developed expansion, anterodorsal view; 49, cercal bridge connecting anterior cerci, anterodorsal view, setae omitted; 50 – 53, paratype ♀. 50, tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view, setae omitted; 51, tergite 8, dorsal view; 52, sternite 8, ventral view; 53, genital fork, ventral view. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus: BS, baciliform sclerite; VPC, ventral projection of cercus. Scales: 45 – 49, 50 – 52 = 0.2 mm; 53 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237985/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
Fig. 
<number box="[211,240,582,607]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="46.0">46</number>
</figureCitation>
) with anterodorsal and posterodorsal lobes short, almost same height. Anterior cercus wider ventrally (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 45 – 53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1842,1865]" captionTargetBox="[191,1395,983,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,983,1820]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 45 – 53. Macrostomus xavieri, sp. nov. 45 – 49, paratype ♂. 45, tergite 8, dorsal view, right setae omitted; 46, epandrium detached, lateral view (gray colored); 47, hypandrium and cerci (cerci gray colored, tergite 8 setae omitted), lateral view; 48, ventral projection of cerci with developed expansion, anterodorsal view; 49, cercal bridge connecting anterior cerci, anterodorsal view, setae omitted; 50 – 53, paratype ♀. 50, tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view, setae omitted; 51, tergite 8, dorsal view; 52, sternite 8, ventral view; 53, genital fork, ventral view. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus: BS, baciliform sclerite; VPC, ventral projection of cercus. Scales: 45 – 49, 50 – 52 = 0.2 mm; 53 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237985/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,182,619,643]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="47.0">47</number>
</figureCitation>
), with internal small process dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[621,706,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURES 45 – 53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1842,1865]" captionTargetBox="[191,1395,983,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,983,1820]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 45 – 53. Macrostomus xavieri, sp. nov. 45 – 49, paratype ♂. 45, tergite 8, dorsal view, right setae omitted; 46, epandrium detached, lateral view (gray colored); 47, hypandrium and cerci (cerci gray colored, tergite 8 setae omitted), lateral view; 48, ventral projection of cerci with developed expansion, anterodorsal view; 49, cercal bridge connecting anterior cerci, anterodorsal view, setae omitted; 50 – 53, paratype ♀. 50, tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view, setae omitted; 51, tergite 8, dorsal view; 52, sternite 8, ventral view; 53, genital fork, ventral view. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus: BS, baciliform sclerite; VPC, ventral projection of cercus. Scales: 45 – 49, 50 – 52 = 0.2 mm; 53 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237985/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
Fig. 
<number box="[674,706,619,643]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="49.0">49</number>
</figureCitation>
); posterior cercus elongate longitudinally, curved inward. Cercal bridge (
<figureCitation box="[240,324,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 45 – 53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1842,1865]" captionTargetBox="[191,1395,983,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,983,1820]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 45 – 53. Macrostomus xavieri, sp. nov. 45 – 49, paratype ♂. 45, tergite 8, dorsal view, right setae omitted; 46, epandrium detached, lateral view (gray colored); 47, hypandrium and cerci (cerci gray colored, tergite 8 setae omitted), lateral view; 48, ventral projection of cerci with developed expansion, anterodorsal view; 49, cercal bridge connecting anterior cerci, anterodorsal view, setae omitted; 50 – 53, paratype ♀. 50, tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view, setae omitted; 51, tergite 8, dorsal view; 52, sternite 8, ventral view; 53, genital fork, ventral view. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus: BS, baciliform sclerite; VPC, ventral projection of cercus. Scales: 45 – 49, 50 – 52 = 0.2 mm; 53 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237985/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
Fig. 
<number box="[295,324,655,679]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="49.0">49</number>
</figureCitation>
) small, projecting anteriorly from ventral margin of anterior cercus. Ventral projection of cercus widened, with setae placed on small protuberance (
<figureCitation box="[753,842,690,715]" captionStart="FIGURES 45 – 53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1842,1865]" captionTargetBox="[191,1395,983,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,983,1820]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 45 – 53. Macrostomus xavieri, sp. nov. 45 – 49, paratype ♂. 45, tergite 8, dorsal view, right setae omitted; 46, epandrium detached, lateral view (gray colored); 47, hypandrium and cerci (cerci gray colored, tergite 8 setae omitted), lateral view; 48, ventral projection of cerci with developed expansion, anterodorsal view; 49, cercal bridge connecting anterior cerci, anterodorsal view, setae omitted; 50 – 53, paratype ♀. 50, tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view, setae omitted; 51, tergite 8, dorsal view; 52, sternite 8, ventral view; 53, genital fork, ventral view. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus: BS, baciliform sclerite; VPC, ventral projection of cercus. Scales: 45 – 49, 50 – 52 = 0.2 mm; 53 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237985/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
Fig. 
<number box="[810,842,691,715]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="48.0">48</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[1027,1112,690,715]" captionStart="FIGURES 45 – 53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1842,1865]" captionTargetBox="[191,1395,983,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,983,1820]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 45 – 53. Macrostomus xavieri, sp. nov. 45 – 49, paratype ♂. 45, tergite 8, dorsal view, right setae omitted; 46, epandrium detached, lateral view (gray colored); 47, hypandrium and cerci (cerci gray colored, tergite 8 setae omitted), lateral view; 48, ventral projection of cerci with developed expansion, anterodorsal view; 49, cercal bridge connecting anterior cerci, anterodorsal view, setae omitted; 50 – 53, paratype ♀. 50, tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view, setae omitted; 51, tergite 8, dorsal view; 52, sternite 8, ventral view; 53, genital fork, ventral view. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus: BS, baciliform sclerite; VPC, ventral projection of cercus. Scales: 45 – 49, 50 – 52 = 0.2 mm; 53 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237985/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
Fig. 
<number box="[1083,1112,691,715]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="47.0">47</number>
</figureCitation>
) with few uniseriated setae medially, without sinus on posterior margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,258,931]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
Female. Fore coxa black; hind femur banded with yellow at base and subapically, black at middle and apically. Mid tibia with 
<number box="[323,337,799,823]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="1.0">1</number>
slightly longer posterodorsal seta near middle. 
<collectingCountry box="[880,936,798,823]" name="India" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia without pinnate setae. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1423,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURES 54 – 63" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1580,1603]" captionTargetBox="[161,1436,193,1544]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[161,1446,193,1545]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54 – 63. Wings. 54, Macrostomus acreanus sp. nov. paratype ♂; 55, M. acreanus sp. nov. paratype ♀; 56, M. albicaudatus sp. nov. paratype ♂; 57, M. albicaudatus sp. nov. paratype ♀; 58, M. amazonensis sp. nov. paratype ♂; 59, M. amazonensis sp. nov. paratype ♀; 60, M. paraiba sp. nov. paratype ♂; 61, M. paraiba sp. nov. paratype ♀; 62, M. xavieri sp. nov. paratype ♂; 63, M. xavieri sp. nov. paratype ♀." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237986/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1423,798,823]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="63.0">63</number>
</figureCitation>
). Terminalia with tergite 
<number box="[416,430,835,859]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="8.0">8</number>
and sternite 
<number box="[576,590,835,859]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="8.0">8</number>
same length (
<figureCitation box="[749,834,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURES 45 – 53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1842,1865]" captionTargetBox="[191,1395,983,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,983,1820]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 45 – 53. Macrostomus xavieri, sp. nov. 45 – 49, paratype ♂. 45, tergite 8, dorsal view, right setae omitted; 46, epandrium detached, lateral view (gray colored); 47, hypandrium and cerci (cerci gray colored, tergite 8 setae omitted), lateral view; 48, ventral projection of cerci with developed expansion, anterodorsal view; 49, cercal bridge connecting anterior cerci, anterodorsal view, setae omitted; 50 – 53, paratype ♀. 50, tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view, setae omitted; 51, tergite 8, dorsal view; 52, sternite 8, ventral view; 53, genital fork, ventral view. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus: BS, baciliform sclerite; VPC, ventral projection of cercus. Scales: 45 – 49, 50 – 52 = 0.2 mm; 53 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237985/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
Fig. 
<number box="[802,834,834,859]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="50.0">50</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tergite 
<number box="[940,954,835,859]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[970,1052,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURES 45 – 53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1842,1865]" captionTargetBox="[191,1395,983,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1398,983,1820]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 45 – 53. Macrostomus xavieri, sp. nov. 45 – 49, paratype ♂. 45, tergite 8, dorsal view, right setae omitted; 46, epandrium detached, lateral view (gray colored); 47, hypandrium and cerci (cerci gray colored, tergite 8 setae omitted), lateral view; 48, ventral projection of cerci with developed expansion, anterodorsal view; 49, cercal bridge connecting anterior cerci, anterodorsal view, setae omitted; 50 – 53, paratype ♀. 50, tergite 8 and sternite 8, lateral view, setae omitted; 51, tergite 8, dorsal view; 52, sternite 8, ventral view; 53, genital fork, ventral view. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus: BS, baciliform sclerite; VPC, ventral projection of cercus. Scales: 45 – 49, 50 – 52 = 0.2 mm; 53 = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237985/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="118">
Fig. 
<number box="[1023,1052,834,859]" pageId="9" pageNumber="118" value="51.0">51</number>
</figureCitation>
) with distal sinus. Sternite 
